本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:郭振民研究生(外文):Kuo Chen Min論文名稱:應用遙測與地理資訊系統於分佈型降雨-逕流模式之研究論文名稱(外文):A Study of Distributed Rainfall-Runoff Model Using Remote Sensing and Geographic Information System指導教授:游保杉指導教授(外文):Yu Pao Shan學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立成功大學系所名稱:水利及海洋工程學系學門:工程學門學類:河海工程學類論文出版年:1999畢業學年度:87語文別:中文論文頁數:93中文關鍵詞:遙測、地理資訊系統、分佈型降雨-逕流模式、全域最佳化方法、土地利用變遷外文關鍵詞:Remote Sensing、Geographic Information System、Distributed Rainfall-Runoff Model、Global Optimization Technique、Land Use Change相關次數:

被引用:33點閱:197評分:下載:0書目收藏:0



本文旨在利用地理資訊系統及遙測技術與分佈型降雨-逕流模式結合，以考慮空間不均勻的水文現象，並探討土地利用變化對設計洪水之影響。為充分模擬集水區內部水文現象之空間變異，本文採用地理資訊系統與遙測技術來建立集水區的地文因子與分析土地利用變遷情形，提供降雨-逕流模式之輸入資料。在模式參數率定過程方面，本研究嘗試採用全域最佳化方法比較傳統的單目標函數法與模糊多目標函數法對模式率定結果之差異，經由率定與驗證發現：使用模糊多目標函數法之率定結果較傳統單目標函數佳。另外，本研究以三種尺度(2公里、1公里、0.5公里)加以探討空間尺度對模擬之影響，經分析結果以1公里較佳。於是以1公里空間尺度分析土地利用變遷對於集水區逕流之影響，由分析結果得知：八掌溪上游集水區之森林逐漸為檳榔所取代，道路與都市地開發也逐漸增加，此種土地利用變遷的情形會使尖峰流量顯著增加。

The study is aimed at estimating the effects of land use change on runoff simulation. A distributed rainfall-runoff model, which can simulate the spatial heterogeneous characters of hydrological process, was used in the study. The GIS and RS techniques was utilized to detect the degree of land use change and to calculate the watershed characters as model input. The global optimization technique coupled with the fuzzy multi-objective function (FMOF) was adopted in the study for model calibration to compare with the single objective function (SOF). From the results of calibration and verification, it reveals that using the FMOF has better performance for runoff simulation than using the traditional method. In order to detect the scale effect on model simulation, three scales (i.e., 0.5, 1, and 2km) were separately used in this study. The modelling results show that the scale of 1km has the best simulation and was further used for analyse the effects of land use change. In the basin of Pa-Chang Creek increasing forest areas on hills replaced by betel nut and impervious area (e.g., roads and urban areas) were discovered by using the GIS and RS techniques. It''s worth noting that the peak discharge significantly increases with the land use change.

